==English==
===[[Pronunciation]]===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]: /&#477;'s&#230;s&#305;n/
===Etymology===
From the French "Assassin" or the Italian "assassino", which adopted the word from the Arabic "hashshashin"
===Noun===
#lit. One who eats [[hashish]]. hist. One of the Muslim fanatics during the Crusades who were sent to murder Christian commanders.
#One whose sole purpose is to kill a high profile figure.
#Verb. assassin (assassined, assassined).
#Same as/see killer.

